    "response_text": "To calculate the area of a circle, we use the formula:\n\n\\[ \\text{Area} = \\pi r^2 \\]\n\nwhere \\( r \\) is the radius of the circle.\n\nGiven that the radius \\( r = 7 \\), we can substitute this value into the formula:\n\n\\[ \\text{Area} = \\pi (7)^2 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Area} = \\pi \\times 49 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Area} = 49\\pi \\]\n\nUsing the approximation \\( \\pi \\approx 3.14159 \\):\n\n\\[ \\text{Area} \\approx 49 \\times 3.14159 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Area} \\approx 153.93804 \\]\n\nSo, the area of the circle is approximately \\( 153.94 \\) square units (rounded to two decimal places).",
